Apple TV Will Offer MLB, NBA Games Live Online, Financial Times Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-10T09:36:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/apple-tv-to-offer-baseball-basketball-live-online-ft-reports.html
  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  signed agreements with
Major League Baseball and the  National Basketball Association 
that will enable Apple TV customers to watch games live online,
the Financial Times reported.  The MLB.TV package costs $100 a season, or $120 for an
enhanced version; the NBA is offering Apple TV users two
options: for $65 a season, they can select seven teams to watch,
and for $100, they will have access to all games, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 